As you have used `flexbox` it is expected behaviour. 

You can have 2 options here.

1) **With flexbox** - You need to add condition so that when `incs` / `exps` array are empty the respective `div` should get hide **(but when both array&#39;s length is not equal it will still show the same height box due to flexbox)**.

```
&lt;div className={styles.container}&gt;
  { props.balance.incs.length &gt; 0 &amp;&amp;   //add condition
    &lt;div className={styles.detailsItem}&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        {props.balance.incs.map(inc =&gt; (
          &lt;DetailsItem item={inc} key={inc.id}/&gt;
        ))}
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  }
  { props.balance.exps.length &gt; 0 &amp;&amp; //add condition
    &lt;div className={styles.detailsItem}&gt;
      &lt;ul&gt;
        {props.balance.exps.map(exp =&gt; (
          &lt;DetailsItem item={exp} key={exp.id}/&gt;
        ))}
      &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  }
&lt;/div&gt;
```

[Demo][1]


